-- Taiwan’s CPC Corp. Shuts No. 4 Naphtha Cracker for Maintenance
-- B y   A n n   K o h
-- 2012-07-03T01:41:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-03/taiwan-s-cpc-corp-shuts-no-4-naphtha-cracker-for-maintenance.html
Taiwan ’s CPC Corp. shut its No. 4
naphtha cracker for at least seven days of maintenance work,
according to two company officials.  The plant in Kaohsiung, Taiwan, was halted this week, 
the officials said, asking not to be identified because of
company policy. The unit can make 385,000 metric tons a year
of ethylene,  according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ann Koh in Singapore at 
